The max scope for a service
Pro tip: if you serve a service worker along with the Service-Worker-Allowed header, you
can specify here a list of max scopes for this worker.
After registering a service worker to control a scope, each time a client in that scope request a
resource from anyplace in the network...
The service worker for that scope enters the game and hijacks the request.
Through event.respondWith() and passing a response object, the service worker can answer
the client's request with a custom response made out of different sources: the network, storage
